cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with 3D vision tasks and proposes a new approach to multiple view aggregation using deep neural networks. This makes it likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also focuses on deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with group convolutions, which are commonly used in geometric deep learning, making the sub-category of Geometric Deep Learning (cs.GR) a likely candidate. Finally, the paper sets a new state of the art in several 3D shape retrieval tasks, indicating that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
